Abstract: 1.0 Abstract A fundamental axiom of computer system design holds that "any software design problem can be solved by adding an extra level of indirection." This paper expresses a variant of this axiom in pattern form as the "Identity Indirection" pattern. This pattern has been used for decades in many different types of systems in the software industry. It is so common that many developers hardly notice it anymore. 
