Reference-contexts: When combined with the Proxy and Factory patterns <ref> [GoF] </ref>, this identity indirection allows client wrappers to be written that have the same binding interface for all services, but different underlying interface implementations. This approach uses an indirect identity on top of the existing toolkit implementations without forcing a change in interface models.
